 camera, but here's a summary 
 of what I found:
 The oil filter was really wet and too easy to
 unscrew!! It was on, but I 
 think there was a gap there. Everything around it
 was oily-ish. The tin next 
 to it was covered in sludge. Passenger's side tin
 was fine.
 There's a little oil seepage from the 4 central
 tubes at the engine top, and 
 it looks from the bottom like the push-rod tube
 seals are leaking. I had a 
 little bit of spray (a pththt) of the old oil out of
 the tailpipe when 
 starting it up after the new oil refill. None since,
  ...so far.
 #4 spark plug had a little white residue, #3 and #1
 were a little oily - not 
 much. #2 I can't remember 'cuz I dropped the blasted
 thing so many times 
 inside the tin - then had to get the new one in.
 Ugh!
 
